    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It could anything, a newsletter, a friendly-phone call, a handshake...anything that keeps the relationship intact.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "I realized recently that many brands do more or less the same thing when they put customer-facing copy on what we might call \"brand artifacts,\" or, 'any physical object a customer uses when interacting a brand.'",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Consider, for example, the copy that",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Sweetgreen",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "and",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Chipotle",
          "marks": [
            "link-1"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "put on their napkins and cups. Even if it's just to tell you that it's disposable, it's an experience that tells a story and that reinforces the customer-brand relationship.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
